3. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper mentions grammatical derivations as an example of the algorithm's output space, which falls under the scope of natural language processing. 
4. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the use of dynamic programming algorithms and their optimization using weighted logic programming. 
5. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) - The paper discusses the computation of Kullback-Leibler divergence, which is a measure commonly used in information theory and discrete mathematics.
